Package: microhaplot
Type: Package
Title: short read variant visualizer
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Thomas", "Ng", email = "tngthomasng@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package has two main functions: 1) to extract microhaplotype from
    individual-based alignment and variant files, specifically from SAM and VCF files
    2) to call and curate microhaplotype with the aid of simple filter criteria and
    summaries plot found in the Shiny App interface.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.2)
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Imports:
    DT (>= 0.1),
    dplyr (>= 0.4.3),
    ggplot2 (>= 2.1.0),
    grid (>= 3.1.2),
    gtools (>= 3.5.0),
    magrittr (>= 1.5),
    scales (>= 0.4.0),
    shiny (>= 0.13.2),
    shinyBS (>= 0.61),
    tidyr (>= 0.4.1),
    shinyWidgets (>= 0.4.3),
    plotly (>= 4.8.0),
URL: https://github.com/ngthomas/microhaplot
BugReports: https://github.com/ngthomas/microhaplot/issues
